<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>SDCI + Cisco SD-WAN | Dual Procurement Paths</title>
  <style>
    :root{
      --bg:#f4f8fc;
      --card:#ffffff;
      --line:#d8e2ee;
      --text:#102a43;
      --muted:#627d98;
      --cisco:#00bceb;
      --cisco-dark:#0b5cab;
      --green:#16a34a;
      --orange:#f59e0b;
      --purple:#7c3aed;
      --shadow:0 10px 24px rgba(16,42,67,.08);
    }
    *{box-sizing:border-box}
    body{
      margin:0;
      font-family:Segoe UI,Roboto,Arial,sans-serif;
      background:var(--bg);
      color:var(--text);
    }
    .container{
      width:min(1180px,94%);
      margin:0 auto;
      padding:22px 0 36px;
    }
    .hero{
      background:linear-gradient(130deg,var(--cisco-dark),var(--cisco));
      color:#fff;
      border-radius:16px;
      padding:24px;
      box-shadow:var(--shadow);
      margin-bottom:16px;
    }
    .hero h1{margin:0 0 8px;font-size:clamp(1.2rem,2.6vw,2rem)}
    .hero p{margin:0;color:#eaf7ff}
    .one-liner{
      margin-top:10px;
      background:rgba(255,255,255,.16);
      border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.35);
      border-radius:10px;
      padding:8px 10px;
      font-size:.9rem;
      color:#fff;
    }
    .chips{margin-top:12px;display:flex;gap:8px;flex-wrap:wrap}
    .chip{
      border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.35);
      background:rgba(255,255,255,.14);
      padding:6px 10px;border-radius:999px;font-size:.82rem
    }

    .grid{
      display:grid;
      grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;
      gap:14px;
      margin-bottom:14px;
    }
    .card{
      background:var(--card);
      border:1px solid var(--line);
      border-radius:14px;
      padding:16px;
      box-shadow:var(--shadow);
    }
    .card h2{margin:0 0 8px;font-size:1.05rem}
    .sub{color:var(--muted);margin:0;font-size:.95rem}

    .lane-title{
      display:flex;align-items:center;gap:8px;margin-bottom:10px
    }
    .dot{width:11px;height:11px;border-radius:99px;display:inline-block}
    .dot-a{background:var(--green)}
    .dot-b{background:var(--orange)}

    .steps{display:grid;gap:8px}
    .step{
      border:1px solid var(--line);
      background:#f9fcff;
      border-radius:10px;
      padding:10px 12px;
      font-size:.93rem;
    }
    .arrow{
      text-align:center;
      color:var(--cisco-dark);
      font-weight:700;
      font-size:1rem;
      margin:2px 0;
    }

    .micro{
      margin-top:10px;
      border:1px solid var(--line);
      background:#f7fbff;
      border-radius:10px;
      padding:10px 12px;
      font-size:.9rem;
      color:#26415d;
    }
    .micro strong{color:#0b3f75}
    .micro ul{margin:6px 0 0;padding-left:18px}
    .micro li{margin-bottom:5px}

    .full{
      background:var(--card);
      border:1px solid var(--line);
      border-radius:14px;
      padding:16px;
      box-shadow:var(--shadow);
      margin-top:10px;
    }

    .pov{
      margin-top:14px;
      border:1px solid var(--line);
      background:#f7fbff;
      border-radius:12px;
      padding:12px;
    }
    .pov h3{margin:0 0 8px}
    .pov p{margin:0 0 8px;color:var(--muted)}
    .pov ul{margin:0;padding-left:18px;color:#26415d}
    .pov li{margin-bottom:6px;font-size:.93rem}

    table{
      width:100%;
      border-collapse:collapse;
      margin-top:8px;
      font-size:.93rem;
    }
    th,td{
      border:1px solid var(--line);
      padding:10px;
      vertical-align:top;
      text-align:left;
    }
    th{background:#eef7ff}
    .tag{
      display:inline-block;
      padding:3px 8px;
      border-radius:999px;
      font-size:.78rem;
      color:#fff;
      font-weight:600;
    }
    .t-a{background:var(--green)}
    .t-b{background:var(--orange)}
    .t-r{background:var(--purple)}

    .timeline{
      margin-top:10px;
      display:grid;
      grid-template-columns:repeat(5,1fr);
      gap:8px;
    }
    .time{
      border:1px dashed var(--line);
      background:#fbfdff;
      border-radius:10px;
      padding:9px;
      text-align:center;
      font-size:.85rem;
    }
    .time strong{display:block;color:var(--cisco-dark)}

    .note{
      margin-top:10px;
      color:var(--muted);
      font-size:.88rem;
    }

    @media(max-width:940px){
      .grid{grid-template-columns:1fr}
      .timeline{grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr}
    }
    @media(max-width:560px){
      .timeline{grid-template-columns:1fr}
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="container">
    <section class="hero">
      <h1>Cisco SD-WAN + SDCI Commercial Framework (Dual Procurement Paths)</h1>
      <p>
        Framework for enterprise and neocloud motions: direct Cisco procurement through Solutions+ / GPL,
        or direct platform activation with quarterly/half-year license credit-back reconciliation.
      </p>

      <div class="one-liner">
        Equinix already has both selling motions in place today: enterprise-led Cisco procurement and platform-led activation with reconciliation.
      </div>

      <div class="chips">
        <span class="chip">Enterprise Seller Motion</span>
        <span class="chip">Neocloud Platform Motion</span>
        <span class="chip">BYOL Support</span>
        <span class="chip">License Credit-Back</span>
        <span class="chip">Q / H Reconciliation</span>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="grid">
      <!-- PATH A -->
      <article class="card">
        <div class="lane-title">
          <span class="dot dot-a"></span>
          <h2>Path A — Enterprise-Led Procurement (Cisco Direct Motion)</h2>
        </div>
        <p class="sub">
          Enterprise account sellers position and sell SDCI through Solutions+ / GPL, attach Cisco SD-WAN HW/SW,
          and support BYOL portability into target neocloud environments.
        </p>
        <div class="steps">
          <div class="step"><strong>1.</strong> Cisco AE identifies AI/Neocloud use case and proposes reference architecture.</div>
          <div class="arrow">↓</div>
          <div class="step"><strong>2.</strong> Enterprise procures <strong>SDCI via Solutions+ / GPL</strong> and selects Cisco SD-WAN components.</div>
          <div class="arrow">↓</div>
          <div class="step"><strong>3.</strong> Cisco SD-WAN HW/SW deployed; policy and segmentation configured for Neocloud access.</div>
          <div class="arrow">↓</div>
          <div class="step"><strong>4.</strong> <strong>BYOL enabled:</strong> enterprise can apply existing eligible Cisco licenses to supported deployments.</div>
          <div class="arrow">↓</div>
          <div class="step"><strong>5.</strong> Enterprise consumes inference services with Cisco-led commercial attribution at sale.</div>
        </div>

        <!-- Enterprise buying programs micro segment -->
        <div class="micro">
          <strong>Enterprise Buying Programs (Micro Segment):</strong>
          Align procurement to existing buying constructs to simplify approvals and expand attach.
          <ul>
            <li><strong>EA’s:</strong> Use enterprise agreement structures for predictable software consumption.</li>
            <li><strong>WPAS:</strong> Use approved buying pathways to streamline SDCI + SD-WAN acquisition cycles.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </article>

      <!-- PATH B -->
      <article class="card">
        <div class="lane-title">
          <span class="dot dot-b"></span>
          <h2>Path B — Neocloud/Platform Direct Activation (Credit-Back Motion)</h2>
        </div>
        <p class="sub">
          End customer activates Cisco SD-WAN feature enablement directly within Neocloud/inferencing marketplaces,
          including partners such as Qumulus, Cirrascale, and Massed Compute.
        </p>
        <div class="steps">
          <div class="step"><strong>1.</strong> Customer signs up with Neocloud provider (e.g., Qumulus, Cirrascale, Massed Compute).</div>
          <div class="arrow">↓</div>
          <div class="step"><strong>2.</strong> Customer enables <strong>Cisco SD-WAN feature</strong> from provider catalog.</div>
          <div class="arrow">↓</div>
          <div class="step"><strong>3.</strong> <strong>BYOL option:</strong> customer brings eligible existing Cisco licenses where supported by the platform model.</div>
          <div class="arrow">↓</div>
          <div class="step"><strong>4.</strong> Usage/subscription data is mapped to eligible Cisco license/SKU attribution rules.</div>
          <div class="arrow">↓</div>
          <div class="step"><strong>5.</strong> Cisco receives <strong>license credit-back</strong> at end of quarter or half-year per partner agreement.</div>
        </div>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section class="full">
      <h2 style="margin:0 0 8px;">Operating Model: Roles, Attribution, and Reconciliation</h2>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Component</th>
            <th>Path A (Enterprise Direct)</th>
            <th>Path B (Neocloud Direct)</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Primary Seller</strong></td>
            <td><span class="tag t-a">Cisco Enterprise Team</span></td>
            <td><span class="tag t-b">Neocloud / Inference Platform</span></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Procurement Vehicle</strong></td>
            <td>Solutions+ / GPL (SDCI + SD-WAN HW/SW) + EA/WPAS alignment</td>
            <td>Marketplace/Product Catalog “Cisco SD-WAN Feature Enablement”</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>BYOL</strong></td>
            <td>Enterprise can bring eligible existing licenses into supported architectures</td>
            <td>Customer can apply eligible licenses in-provider where partner supports BYOL workflow</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Revenue Recognition Trigger</strong></td>
            <td>At point of enterprise order</td>
            <td>At reconciliation cycle based on reported activations/usage</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Cisco Attribution</strong></td>
            <td>Immediate (deal registered/closed)</td>
            <td><span class="tag t-r">License Credit-Back (Q / H)</span></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Data Needed</strong></td>
            <td>Customer account, SKU, install base</td>
            <td>Customer ID mapping, platform instance ID, usage period, eligible SKU table</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <div class="pov">
        <h3>End-User POV and Business Implications</h3>
        <p>
          Most end customers care about speed, price, performance, and support outcomes—not internal route mechanics.
          If experience is equivalent, Cisco should prioritize the motion that maximizes attach and efficiency.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Path A:</strong> Familiar enterprise procurement model, centralized sourcing controls, and programmatic buying (EA/WPAS).</li>
          <li><strong>Path B:</strong> Fast in-platform activation through neocloud ecosystems (Qumulus, Cirrascale, Massed Compute), plus BYOL flexibility where supported.</li>
          <li><strong>Why both benefit Cisco:</strong> Neocloud route enables direct sell-through with credit-back; enterprise route drives SDCI via Solutions+ / GPL and keeps AEs incented.</li>
          <li><strong>Incentive alignment:</strong> Enterprise AEs are motivated to push business to neoclouds because SDCI and attribution models maintain compensation linkage.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <h3 style="margin:14px 0 6px;">Reconciliation Timeline (Example)</h3>
      <div class="timeline">
        <div class="time"><strong>Month 1</strong>Platform activations start</div>
        <div class="time"><strong>Month 2</strong>Usage accrual + account mapping</div>
        <div class="time"><strong>Month 3</strong>Quarter close data freeze</div>
        <div class="time"><strong>Month 4</strong>Partner validation + dispute window</div>
        <div class="time"><strong>Month 5</strong>Cisco license credit-back posted</div>
      </div>

      <p class="note">
        Note: Define partner contract controls for BYOL eligibility, SKU crosswalk, reporting cadence, field-comp alignment, and audit rights.
      </p>
    </section>
  </div>
</body>
</html>
